{{2014BWFWorldChampionship}}
The '''2014 [[BWF World Championships]]''' were held from 25 to 31 August 2014 at the [[Ballerup Super Arena]] in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bwfbadminton.org/page.aspx?id=25866 | title=2014 BWF World Championships | publisher=BWF | accessdate=2014-04-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504185501/http://www.bwfbadminton.org/page.aspx?id=25866 | archive-date=2014-05-04 | dead-url=yes | df= }}</ref>

==Host city selection==
[[Copenhagen]] and [[Macau]] submitted bids for this of championships.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sachetat|first1=Raphaël|title=WORLDS 2013 – Macau, Copenhagen and Guangzhou|url=http://www.badzine.net/2011/09/worlds-2013-macau-copenhagen-and-guangzhou/|website=Badzine.net|accessdate=18 March 2017}}</ref> Both cities also bid for the 2013 edition, which was later won by Guangzhou. On 9 December 2011, [[Badminton World Federation]] decided to award the championships to Copenhagen during a meeting in [[Queenstown, New Zealand]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=Guangzhou, Copenhagen to host 2013 and 2014 badminton worlds|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/687952.shtml|website=Global Times|accessdate=18 March 2017}}</ref>

==Draw==
The draw was held on 11 August 2014 at the [[Berjaya Times Square]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]].

==Schedule==
All five events started on the first day and concluded with the final on the last day.<ref>[http://www.bwfbadminton.org/file.aspx?id=558582&dl=1 Schedule]</ref>

''All times are local ([[Central European Summer Time|UTC+2]]).''

